A '''Backing Band''' (in American usage '''Backup Band''') is a group of musicians who accompany an artiste at a live performance or on a recording.  This can either be an established group, for example [[The Shadows]] with [[Cliff Richard]], the [[E Street Band]] with [[Bruce Springsteen]] or [[The Band]] with [[Bob Dylan]], or else an ad hoc group assembled for the purpose.  Such groups are often made up of [[Session musician|session musicians]].